.SH NAME
commitbrief-init - Write COMMITBRIEF.md and a per-user OUTPUT.md template


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcommitbrief init [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Writes two files:
  - COMMITBRIEF.md at the repo root (team-shared review content)
  - .commitbrief/OUTPUT.md (per-user output format template; gitignored)
Both fall back to embedded defaults at runtime, so creating these files
is only necessary when you want to customize the prompt.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for init


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
